// # Shavian QWERTY (or Shaw QWERTY) keyboard layout
// Copyright (c) 2025 Neil Raiden (AGPL v.3)
// <https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.en.html>

// This is a classic Shavian(QWERTY) layout based on early fonts from 1990s which replaced regular Latin alphabet symbols with Shavian symbols.
// This layout, on Layer 3 and 4, contains extra symbols (mostly punctuation marks) that are required by most writing style guides. See Writer(QWERTY) layout for details.

// ## Installation:
// 1. Copy this file (shavian) to `/etc/xkb/symbols/shavian`
//```
//  sudo mkdir -p /etc/xkb/rules
//  sudo mkdir -p /etc/xkb/symbols
//  sudo cp shavian /etc/xkb/symbols/
//```
// 2. Add the following section to `/etc/xkb/rules/evdev.xml`:
//```
//<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
//<!DOCTYPE xkbConfigRegistry SYSTEM "xkb.dtd">
//<xkbConfigRegistry version="1.1">
//  <layoutList>
//<!-- Shavian QWERTY Layout (start) -->
//    <layout>
//      <configItem>
//        <name>shavian</name>
//        <shortDescription>Shavian</shortDescription>
//        <description>Shavian (QWERTY)</description>
//        <countryList><iso3166Id>US</iso3166Id></countryList>
//        <languageList><iso639Id>eng</iso639Id></languageList>
//      </configItem>
//    </layout>
//<!-- Shavian QWERTY Layout (end) -->
//  </layoutList>
//</xkbConfigRegistry>
//```
// 3. (optional) add the following line to `/etc/xkb/rules/evdev`. Note that GNOME layout switcher ignores the `evdev` file and uses only the `evdev.xml`:
//```
//! option = symbols
//  shavian:qwerty    = +shavian(qwerty)
//! include %S/evdev
//```
// 4. Testing:
//	- activate "Shavian (QWERTY)": `setxkbmap -layout shavian`,
//  - test it by simply typing with the new layout,
//  - if setxkbmap returns "Error loading new keyboard description", then it's possible that your Linux distro runs xkb with elevated privileges and ignores files in `/etc/xkb/symbols`. In such case create a link: `sudo ln -s /etc/xkb/symbols/shavian /usr/share/X11/xkb/symbols/shavian`,
//	- reset back to default layout: `setxkbmap us`

// ------ Layer 1 (unshifted) ------
